  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The study was aimed to investigate the role of cognition and asymmetric dopaminergic
      depletion in FoG.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
  <detailed_description>
    <textblock>
      Alteration of cortical circuits in PD leads to cognitive dysfunctions associated with the
      development of FoG. The asymmetric degeneration of the corticostriatal dopaminergic circuits
      affects differently cognition in PD patients with right side (RPD) and left side (LPD) motor
      symptoms onset.

      The study was aimed to investigate the role of cognition and asymmetric dopaminergic
      depletion in FoG.
    </textblock>
  </detailed_description>
